HDHRUtil-Tuner-channelSettingSave - Save the channel status to a file


usage: HDHRUtil-Tuner-channelSettingSave [-h] --hdhr HDHR [--outfile OUTFILE] [--use-cloud-discovery]

options:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --hdhr HDHR           the HDHomeRun to manage
  --outfile OUTFILE, --output-file OUTFILE
                        the file to store the settings
  --use-cloud-discovery
                        use the SiliconDust Cloud API services to discover local tuners



Scenario:

You want to save the channel settings from HDHR to a file

   HDHRUtil-Tuner-channelSettingSave --hdhr=hdhr1.local --outfile hdhr1.settings

